WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:06.320 --> 00:00:08.760
Let us be a little, well, immodest,
but it really is beautiful!

00:00:08.760 --> 00:00:13.760
I tried to make the animals appear alive.

00:00:13.760 --> 00:00:17.400
To be quite honest,
it was one of the most important days in

00:00:17.400 --> 00:00:22.440
my career at the time,
perhaps even my entire career.

00:00:22.440 --> 00:00:25.760
There were tears,
there were such touching moments,

00:00:25.760 --> 00:00:29.720
that I get goose bumps even
now when I think about it.

00:00:29.720 --> 00:00:34.320
Young men, 20 years old,
were lining up to go to war,

00:00:34.320 --> 00:00:36.040
and there we were, introducing
the kuna, a hard currency. 

00:00:36.040 --> 00:00:37.640
People laughed at us...

00:00:37.640 --> 00:00:41.880
After all, this was a unique moment
in the life of an average man,

00:00:41.880 --> 00:00:44.960
the creation of something
which would define the state,

00:00:44.960 --> 00:00:46.920
the chance to participate in this.

00:00:46.920 --> 00:00:50.600
It was a great 
pleasure and a great honour for us all.

00:01:56.800 --> 00:02:01.800
Dr. sc. Hrvoje Klasić, historian
It was the beginning of Croatia’s final
phase of disassociation,

00:02:01.800 --> 00:02:05.600
Dr. sc. Hrvoje Klasić, historian
its independence and
dissolution from Yugoslavia.

00:02:05.600 --> 00:02:09.960
Unfortunately, the process was
neither smooth nor painless,

00:02:09.960 --> 00:02:15.120
in the political sense, both internally and in 
regards to foreign policy,

00:02:15.120 --> 00:02:20.720
but it was also painful from a
military aspect.

00:02:21.800 --> 00:02:26.480
Dr. sc. Franjo Gregurić
Prime Minister of the Republic of Croatia
from 1991 to 1992
On the one hand, it was the start
of the former Yugo-army’s

00:02:26.480 --> 00:02:29.440
Dr. sc. Franjo Gregurić
Prime Minister of the Republic of Croatia
from 1991 to 1992
departure from the territory of the
Republic of Croatia, which we had demanded,

00:02:29.440 --> 00:02:32.640
Dr. sc. Franjo Gregurić
Prime Minister of the Republic of Croatia
from 1991 to 1992
while on the other,
there was revolt among

00:02:32.640 --> 00:02:36.480
some of the Serbian population
in Croatia.

00:02:36.480 --> 00:02:42.840
In this atmosphere, it was
necessary to secure a normal life,

00:02:42.840 --> 00:02:46.000
manufacture, jobs, financing.

00:03:06.360 --> 00:03:08.400
Mr. sc. Zdravko Rogić
Deputy Governor of the NBC
(later renamed HNB) from 1990 to 2000
On June 27, Governor Ante Čičin-Šain
and I arrived and familiarized

00:03:08.400 --> 00:03:10.440
Mr. sc. Zdravko Rogić
Deputy Governor of the NBC
(later renamed HNB) from 1990 to 2000
ourselves with the materials,
documents presented to us.

00:03:10.440 --> 00:03:13.480
Mr. sc. Zdravko Rogić
Deputy Governor of the NBC
(later renamed HNB) from 1990 to 2000
We realized they amounted to
a collection of punitive measures

00:03:13.480 --> 00:03:18.280
wholly unconnected to the actions
of the national bank

00:03:18.280 --> 00:03:23.200
and banks in Croatia within the bounds
of monetary policy and system.

00:03:23.200 --> 00:03:26.560
They had all the practical
characteristics of punishment,

00:03:26.560 --> 00:03:32.160
sanctions for the decision in favour
of sovereignty and independence.

00:03:34.120 --> 00:03:39.880
Mr. sc. Borislav Škegro
National Bank of Croatia (NBC) Council member
from 1992 to 1997
Well, one of the methods by which
they thought they would achieve

00:03:39.880 --> 00:03:42.680
Mr. sc. Borislav Škegro
National Bank of Croatia (NBC) Council member
from 1992 to 1997
 something significant was a sort of
expulsion from the monetary system,

00:03:42.680 --> 00:03:45.240
thus the denial of loans from the primary
issue and some other benefits

00:03:45.240 --> 00:03:48.440
the economies could have
gained in that moment.

00:03:48.440 --> 00:03:54.320
Military aggression on Slovenia
began on the 27th, but in a way,

00:03:54.320 --> 00:04:00.680
the decisions, and there were
several made that day,

00:04:00.680 --> 00:04:04.160
represented a form of financial aggression
against Slovenia and Croatia.

00:04:20.560 --> 00:04:24.800
In addition to the recommendation
from the federal government to 

00:04:24.800 --> 00:04:27.160
the national bank and its Board of Governors,

00:04:27.160 --> 00:04:37.040
on July 10 a letter was sent by
 Stane Brovet, general Kadijević’s deputy.

00:04:37.040 --> 00:04:40.360
In this letter – and I believe this
 was very significant

00:04:40.360 --> 00:04:44.040
– he requested for the federal
 government’s recommendation

00:04:44.040 --> 00:04:46.080
not to be implemented.

00:04:46.080 --> 00:04:51.080
Ultimately, this was a case of a departmental
mutiny against the federal government, 

00:04:51.080 --> 00:05:00.160
and clearly, the Board of Governors
listened to the Yugoslav National Army (JNA).

00:05:00.160 --> 00:05:05.360
This made it obvious who was in charge
in Yugoslavia, even at this early stage.

00:05:05.360 --> 00:05:08.640
Croatia at that moment was not
internationally recognised,

00:05:08.640 --> 00:05:14.640
independent country, it was in
an interregnum, so to speak.

00:05:14.640 --> 00:05:20.640
De facto, it was no longer a part of Yugoslavia
while legally remaining so,

00:05:20.640 --> 00:05:23.640
while on the other hand it was
still not a sovereign state.

00:05:23.640 --> 00:05:28.600
Her Its institutions were prevented
from performing those functions

00:05:28.600 --> 00:05:33.360
that are simply not available to a
country which officially does not exist yet.

00:05:35.880 --> 00:05:40.880
INTRODUCTION OF THE CROATIAN DINAR

00:06:38.440 --> 00:06:41.920
Prof. dr. Marijan Hanžeković
chairman of the Commission
As you can see, the Commission
consists of members of Parliament 

00:06:41.920 --> 00:06:46.480
Prof. dr. Marijan Hanžeković
chairman of the Commission
and members of the
 Government – politicians

00:06:46.480 --> 00:06:52.720
and ministers, as well as members
of the professional services. 

00:06:52.720 --> 00:07:02.360
It is very uniformly composed
which has reflected well in our work -

00:07:02.360 --> 00:07:11.680
our first meeting was on August 27,
and we have met 15 times since then.

00:07:11.680 --> 00:07:15.720
We have put in our best effort and
I hope we have successfully

00:07:15.720 --> 00:07:18.840
completed the task.

00:07:56.000 --> 00:08:00.040
Zlatko Jakuš
graphic artist and engraver
author of the Croatian dinar
Thus emerged a currency which
did not even have a name,

00:08:00.040 --> 00:08:03.320
Zlatko Jakuš
graphic artist and engraver
author of the Croatian dinar
but it was money which had to be
issued with the recognition of Croatia.

00:08:03.320 --> 00:08:10.240
From the conceptual design
and agreement on the name,

00:08:10.240 --> 00:08:17.200
appearance, colour scheme and dimensions,
to printing the first banknotes,

00:08:17.200 --> 00:08:21.560
it took three months
– an absolute world record. 

00:08:21.560 --> 00:08:27.080
The money was printed in Sweden,
as you know, and the Swedes introduced

00:08:27.080 --> 00:08:34.480
a special third shift to work in order to
deliver the Croatian dinar on time.

00:08:52.480 --> 00:08:55.000
They are of very good quality
 and safe from counterfeiting;

00:08:55.000 --> 00:08:57.480
Dr. sc. Ante Čičin-Šain
first Governor of the NBC
They are of very good quality
 and safe from counterfeiting;

00:08:57.480 --> 00:09:01.320
Dr. sc. Ante Čičin-Šain
first Governor of the NBC
 they have nine different
 elements of protection.

00:09:02.600 --> 00:09:09.120
The banknote is of such quality there is
practically no fear of counterfeiting.

00:09:10.000 --> 00:09:15.480
Nikola Raguž
Currency Department director at the
NBC from 1991 to 1994
The first contingent of banknotes arrived
 from Sweden by plane.

00:09:15.480 --> 00:09:17.440
Nikola Raguž
Currency Department director at the
NBC from 1991 to 1994
It was intended to land in Zagreb but
due to the EU-wide embargo on Croatia,

00:09:24.120 --> 00:09:27.560
the plane landed in Graz, Austria.

00:09:27.560 --> 00:09:37.560
It was then transferred to trucks and driven
to the central bank vaults in Zagreb.

00:10:01.680 --> 00:10:05.840
Mr. sc. Borislav Škegro
NBC Council member from 1992 to 1997
Formally, legally, it was not currency,
there were political reasons for this. 

00:10:05.840 --> 00:10:09.800
Mr. sc. Borislav Škegro
NBC Council member from 1992 to 1997
The Croatian state leadership at that
moment did not want to give rise either 

00:10:09.800 --> 00:10:13.280
either to the other member-states
of the former federation

00:10:13.280 --> 00:10:14.760
or to the international community.

00:10:15.400 --> 00:10:21.320
Mr. sc. Bogomil Cota
director-general of the Croatian branch
of the Social Accounting Service
and Commission member
We agreed to substitute the Yugoslav dinar
with the Croatian dinar

00:10:21.320 --> 00:10:26.120
over a period of five days, between
December 27 and December 31.

00:10:26.120 --> 00:10:33.400
Just before this there were further discussions
in the Government and wider afield, 

00:10:33.400 --> 00:10:39.680
and it was decided to begin the replacement
before Christmas and the New Year

00:10:39.680 --> 00:10:45.040
so the numerous Croatian workers
living in Germany and other countries

00:10:45.040 --> 00:10:51.720
could exchange their currency for the
Croatian dinar when they visited.

00:10:51.720 --> 00:10:53.960
This was the main reason.

00:10:53.960 --> 00:10:59.400
The process of substituting the currency
is flowing very well, very calmly. 

00:10:59.400 --> 00:11:05.840
Exchanges are happening in all parts of Croatia,
with almost no impediment, delays.

00:11:05.840 --> 00:11:09.920
This is equally the case in both
Eastern Slavonia and Dubrovnik,

00:11:09.920 --> 00:11:12.640
I do not even have to
mention the other regions.

00:11:12.640 --> 00:11:19.880
The plan was for the central bank
to distribute the Croatian dinar

00:11:19.880 --> 00:11:23.160
in cooperation with
the Social Accounting Service.

00:11:23.160 --> 00:11:29.680
Unfortunately, we were denied
access to our occupied areas 

00:11:29.680 --> 00:11:33.800
but there were many other territories
directly imperilled by the war.

00:11:33.800 --> 00:11:37.920
Nikola Raguž
Currency Department director
at the NBC from 1991 to 1994
Dalmatia was also cut off.

00:11:37.920 --> 00:11:45.120
Nikola Raguž
Currency Department director
at the NBC from 1991 to 1994
Of course, we drove the money anyway,
 by truck over the island of Pag to Zadar,

00:11:45.120 --> 00:11:52.920
Šibenik and Split and ferried it by sea
from Rijeka to Split and Dubrovnik.

00:11:52.920 --> 00:11:59.040
When currency is substituted in this way,
the obvious issue was that certain

00:11:59.040 --> 00:12:06.160
Dr. sc. Jozo Martinović
Finance Minister from 1991 to 1992
restrictions had to be enforced
to ensure illegal and problem dinars,

00:12:06.160 --> 00:12:09.000
Dr. sc. Jozo Martinović
Finance Minister from 1991 to 1992
problematic banknotes would not
appear and be mistaken for real money. 

00:12:09.000 --> 00:12:13.160
With this in mind, the Commission evaluated
that it would be enough

00:12:13.160 --> 00:12:21.640
for every Croatian citizen to exchange
10000 Yugoslav dinars for an equal amount,

00:12:21.640 --> 00:12:23.800
10000 Croatian dinars.

00:12:23.800 --> 00:12:29.000
Franjo Gregurić
Prime Minister of the Republic of Croatia
from 1991 to 1992
It was the first of all the activities
which led up to the forging of an 

00:12:29.000 --> 00:12:33.160
independent and sovereign Croatian state,

00:12:33.160 --> 00:12:39.520
and can be characterised on the
one hand as part of a great effort

00:12:39.520 --> 00:12:42.600
of goodwill towards the international community,

00:12:42.600 --> 00:12:45.760
something done to prove ourselves
and create stable conditions

00:12:45.760 --> 00:12:47.080
in an effort to gain international recognition.

00:13:19.400 --> 00:13:26.640
Dalibor Brozović
Member of the Croatian Academy
of Sciences and Arts, Commission member
The long-term solution,
to be implemented when the monetary

00:13:26.640 --> 00:13:31.440
is the crown, divided
into a hundred banica.

00:13:46.000 --> 00:13:51.680
Dr. sc. Nedjeljko Mihanović
Commission member and president
of the Parliament Committee for Education,
Science, Culture and Sport from 1990 to 1994
The marten, at least its pelt, was in fact
a form of currency as early as the 13th century.

00:13:51.680 --> 00:13:54.999
People bartered
pelts for other goods…

00:13:55.000 --> 00:14:02.720
Dr. sc. Franjo Tuđman
first Croatian President
The marten was a means of payment
in ages long gone in the Croatian territories,

00:14:02.720 --> 00:14:04.640
from Slavonia to Istria.

00:14:04.640 --> 00:14:11.240
The kuna’s pelt was accepted as a means
of payment in other parts of the world, 

00:14:11.240 --> 00:14:17.160
too, but I do not know of any other
country that gave the pelt as much

00:14:17.160 --> 00:14:21.320
significance as it has throughout Croatian history
and the Croatian national consciousness. 

00:14:21.320 --> 00:14:25.720
Namely, the kuna is depicted on the historic
coat of arms of the ancient

00:14:25.720 --> 00:14:29.240
Croatian kingdom of Slavonia.

00:14:52.000 --> 00:14:58.320
Nikica Valentić
Prime Minister of the Republic of Croatia
from 1993 to 1995
We were under a lot of pressure because the kuna
bears the burden of the fact that it was also

00:14:58.320 --> 00:15:02.120
the currency during the time of the so-called
“Independent State of Croatia” (NDH). 

00:15:02.120 --> 00:15:05.720
This was a completely insignificant
period in the Croatian history.

00:15:05.720 --> 00:15:10.600
That entity was not a true state,
legally or in any other sense.

00:15:10.600 --> 00:15:14.880
The fact that for a couple
of years someone used something

00:15:14.880 --> 00:15:17.999
that had lasted for centuries before,
is not a valid reason for it to be discredited.

00:15:18.920 --> 00:15:23.080
TENDER FOR COINS

00:15:54.520 --> 00:15:56.880
First, I should point out that
 Member of the Croatian Academy

00:15:56.880 --> 00:15:59.240
of Sciences and Arts,
professor Brozović

00:15:59.240 --> 00:16:04.520
was the most responsible for the
 issuing of the Croatian currency,

00:16:04.520 --> 00:16:07.320
especially minted coins.

00:16:07.520 --> 00:16:12.720
Nikola Raguž
Currency Department director at the
NBC from 1991 to 1994
He dealt with the history of
numismatics in his works,

00:16:12.720 --> 00:16:19.999
Nikola Raguž
Currency Department director at the
NBC from 1991 to 1994
 was a keen numismatist himself,
so he had the best overview.

00:16:19.999 --> 00:16:26.320
We worked together a great deal,
but my part was more technical in nature.

00:16:26.520 --> 00:16:31.560
Calculations had to be done:
there were nine coins,

00:16:31.560 --> 00:16:34.800
it was necessary to calculate
their dimensions: diameter,

00:16:34.800 --> 00:16:37.840
size, thickness, weight. 

00:16:38.600 --> 00:16:43.160
Kuzma Kovačić sent in the best
complete visual design, 

00:16:43.160 --> 00:16:48.960
first a set of beautiful drawings,
then plaster models.

00:16:48.960 --> 00:16:55.960
Prof. Igor Zidić, Commission member
He was young at the time,
but already a great sculptor

00:16:55.960 --> 00:16:59.640
in the finest Croatian tradition.

00:16:59.640 --> 00:17:04.320
It was evident that his sculpting
skills were special,

00:17:04.320 --> 00:17:09.080
extraordinary, and it
was fully expressed here.

00:17:09.080 --> 00:17:14.400
Unburdened by history and tradition,
he allowed himself to be playful in

00:17:14.400 --> 00:17:18.280
his fine modelling and there was
absolutely no dispute within

00:17:18.280 --> 00:17:20.999
the Commission concerning his selection.

00:17:33.800 --> 00:17:42.200
In looking for a new visual design,
the art concept,

00:17:42.200 --> 00:17:51.720
Prof. dr. Kuzma Kovačić
sculptor, author of the kuna and lipa coins
in a way I really relied on the beauty of the old,
primarily antique coinage,

00:17:51.720 --> 00:17:57.160
money that has always been beautifully sculpted,

00:17:57.160 --> 00:18:01.440
not simply numismatically interesting and beautiful.

00:18:01.440 --> 00:18:08.000
That joy, the birth of a sovereign state,
gaining national, renewed freedom,

00:18:08.000 --> 00:18:13.720
it was an inspiration and a motive.

00:18:13.720 --> 00:18:19.040
I approached it this way and
I think in the end

00:18:19.040 --> 00:18:21.760
I succeeded with a beautiful resolution.

00:18:24.240 --> 00:18:27.080
TENDER FOR BANKNOTES

00:18:59.000 --> 00:19:02.720
Prof. Igor Zidić, Commission member
I suggested that at least one piece of currency,
one banknote should contain

00:19:02.720 --> 00:19:05.640
Prof. Igor Zidić, Commission member
the portrait of a prominent Croatian woman. 

00:19:05.640 --> 00:19:07.520
I felt it was bad there were no women,

00:19:07.520 --> 00:19:12.400
and I remember Brozović told me women
would be included in the second series.

00:19:12.400 --> 00:19:14.720
He said it was too late to
go back to the drawing board;

00:19:14.720 --> 00:19:16.320
we would lose too much time.

00:19:16.320 --> 00:19:19.920
I said there are several women
we must not forget, 

00:19:19.920 --> 00:19:22.440
and mentioned Ivana Brlić Mažuranić.

00:19:23.240 --> 00:19:28.120
Dr. sc. Nedjeljko Mihanović
Commission member and president
of the Parliament Committee for Education,
Science, Culture and Sport from 1990 to 1994
The Commission’s idea was to use
the designs of the currency,

00:19:28.120 --> 00:19:31.640
Dr. sc. Nedjeljko Mihanović
Commission member and president
of the Parliament Committee for Education,
Science, Culture and Sport from 1990 to 1994
which had already been planned
in denominations of 

00:19:31.640 --> 00:19:39.440
10, 20, 100, 200, 500 and 1000 kuna,
to cover the entire territory of Croatia.

00:19:55.520 --> 00:19:58.040
There was a lot of controversy.

00:19:58.040 --> 00:20:01.120
I wondered how it is that we
could not decide on Zadar, 

00:20:01.120 --> 00:20:05.040
but there it is, it was not
selected for the simple reason

00:20:05.040 --> 00:20:08.080
that we could choose only eight,
and Croatia really has more than

00:20:08.080 --> 00:20:12.080
eight important historical cities.

00:20:12.080 --> 00:20:17.400
Certainly nobody would have had anything
against Šibenik and its cathedral,

00:20:17.400 --> 00:20:20.920
perhaps the single most important piece
of the Croatian art

00:20:20.920 --> 00:20:28.200
- as the work of our hands,
our minds, in our city.

00:20:28.200 --> 00:20:33.400
At that time of war, we believed that
money is not only an aesthetic object,

00:20:33.400 --> 00:20:38.440
but something that sends a message,
something to identify with.

00:20:40.960 --> 00:20:44.120
SELECTED DESIGN FOR BANKNOTES

00:21:17.480 --> 00:21:20.400
Prof. Igor Zidić, Commission member
Within the Commission,
we created an external,

00:21:20.400 --> 00:21:24.520
expert committee who were responsible
for the recommendations;

00:21:24.520 --> 00:21:29.520
a professional choice, to be verified
or corrected by the Commission

00:21:29.520 --> 00:21:32.999
depending on the final decision.

00:21:32.999 --> 00:21:36.560
Some of them did not even have enough time,

00:21:36.560 --> 00:21:40.960
the deadlines were very tight,
it was burdensome.

00:21:40.960 --> 00:21:43.920
The submissions were short,
we were in a terrible hurry.

00:21:47.920 --> 00:21:49.880
SELECTED DESIGN FOR BANKNOTES

00:21:58.240 --> 00:22:03.280
Two of the most complete works were
by Šutej and Ljubičić,

00:22:03.280 --> 00:22:07.280
the difference being that from the beginning,
Šutej's work was somehow better defined,

00:22:07.280 --> 00:22:12.360
from head to toe as it were.
 All the banknotes, obverse, reverse.

00:22:12.360 --> 00:22:18.760
Everything was included in his project,
while Ljubičić was really giving only samples; 

00:22:18.760 --> 00:22:22.640
the obverse of one banknote, the reverse of another.

00:22:22.640 --> 00:22:27.480
I think he had three or four banknotes
while Šutej had all eight,

00:22:27.480 --> 00:22:33.920
which probably greatly influenced
the members of the Commission.

00:23:00.120 --> 00:23:05.560
Prof. dr. Vilko Žiljak
co-author of the kuna banknotes
Mr Šutej, my friend and colleague,
is primarily an artist, 

00:23:05.560 --> 00:23:16.520
Prof. dr. Vilko Žiljak
co-author of the kuna banknotes
so the deliberacy of the arrangement and
the choice of visual elements were led by him.

00:23:16.840 --> 00:23:21.160
It was a wonderful connection
between two men who fully

00:23:21.160 --> 00:23:24.600
understood the intricacies.

00:23:24.600 --> 00:23:32.120
We did a professional job, the same as
for any banknote in the world.

00:23:34.760 --> 00:23:38.160
PRODUCTION

00:23:48.120 --> 00:23:50.800
We minted the coins in
a very short period of time.

00:23:50.800 --> 00:23:55.440
Dr. sc. Đuro Črnjak
first director of
the Croatian Monetary Institute (HNZ)
In eight months we completed everything,
from the initial decisions to establish

00:23:55.440 --> 00:24:02.680
the HNZ to the realisation
of the first minting.

00:24:02.680 --> 00:24:08.880
The Commercial Services Agency and
the National Bank were in this project together.

00:24:21.240 --> 00:24:24.680
We had the tools made at the Stuttgart mint;

00:24:24.680 --> 00:24:29.040
member of the Croatian Academy of Sciences
and Arts Brozović, Kuzma Kovačić and I 

00:24:29.040 --> 00:24:35.440
visited them several times and corrected some things
with which the author was not satisfied.

00:24:35.440 --> 00:24:41.000
One anecdote I would like to
mention was the 5 kuna coin,

00:24:41.000 --> 00:24:44.880
which depicts a bear on the reverse.

00:24:44.880 --> 00:24:51.999
Kuzma had designed a wonderful
sculpturally rich solution and insisted

00:24:51.999 --> 00:24:59.480
on the bear being beautiful and sturdy
as in the design chosen by the HNB Commission.

00:24:59.480 --> 00:25:06.400
We had a bit of trouble there, since we again had
to cut costs so we ordered relatively thin plates

00:25:06.400 --> 00:25:12.920
from the Royal Mint and there
was not enough space.

00:25:12.920 --> 00:25:19.640
Regardless of the deadline pressures and
everything else, after a few iterations,

00:25:19.640 --> 00:25:24.360
we managed to find a solution
which pleased the author

00:25:24.360 --> 00:25:28.560
while remaining feasible due to
the thinness of the minting plate.

00:26:00.160 --> 00:26:05.480
Prof. dr. Vilko Žiljak
co-author of the kuna banknotes
Vector graphics were ideal at that
time and we raised it to a new, immense level.

00:26:05.480 --> 00:26:10.600
Prof. dr. Vilko Žiljak
co-author of the kuna banknotes
I can now say it was a miracle that it succeeded.

00:26:10.600 --> 00:26:19.000
However, we had to use a high resolution photo unit,
huge for the time,

00:26:19.000 --> 00:26:23.160
then we had extraordinary programs.

00:26:23.160 --> 00:26:30.880
We created a beautiful little group of people
who were absolutely devoted to this task,

00:26:30.880 --> 00:26:33.840
which had no set working hours.

00:26:33.840 --> 00:26:39.600
Wages had also been adjusted to wages in general.
It was nothing excessive.

00:26:57.680 --> 00:27:05.600
Boris Raguž
Currency Department director, HNB
We investigated and found that indeed
Croats working there fraudulently 

00:27:05.600 --> 00:27:13.160
used our 10 kuna as payment
instead of the 10 DM note.

00:27:13.160 --> 00:27:22.560
It became so widespread that the Bundesbank
asked us to consider the possibility

00:27:22.560 --> 00:27:32.720
of replacing this banknote with a new series,
which would be visibly different

00:27:32.720 --> 00:27:41.400
- especially in colouring - from the 10 DM they
had put into circulation two years previously.

00:27:45.320 --> 00:27:48.360
STABILISATION PROGRAMME

00:28:01.920 --> 00:28:03.760
First of all, we were at war. 

00:28:03.760 --> 00:28:07.720
Nikica Valentić
Prime Minister of the Republic of Croatia
from 1993 to 1995
Metaphorically speaking, the entire southern
part of Croatia and Bosnia and part of Herzegovina 

00:28:07.720 --> 00:28:10.320
- which is economically dependent on Croatia

00:28:10.320 --> 00:28:13.680
- were relying on the strength of
two damaged pillars on Pag bridge.

00:28:13.880 --> 00:28:16.680
Two-thirds of Croatia was
under threat of potential war 

00:28:16.680 --> 00:28:18.680
while the last third was already occupied.

00:28:18.680 --> 00:28:21.320
It was a dilemma: either have a wartime economy,

00:28:21.320 --> 00:28:26.400
meaning scattered distribution
and wartime production,

00:28:26.400 --> 00:28:30.040
or an embryo market economy,
which we opted for.

00:28:30.040 --> 00:28:34.920
Mr. sc. Borislav Škegro
NBC Council member from 1992 to 1997 
Prior to launching the stabilisation programme,
President Tudjman tasked

00:28:34.920 --> 00:28:39.240
us in a way with the
success of this programme 

00:28:39.240 --> 00:28:42.520
- stabilize the currency before
the introduction of the kuna.

00:28:42.520 --> 00:28:44.760
We certainly would not have
introduced the kuna

00:28:44.760 --> 00:28:47.000
if the stabilisation programme had failed.

00:28:47.000 --> 00:28:51.080
Inflation was at 36 percent
in the final month.

00:28:51.080 --> 00:28:55.600
By some estimates, in three to six months
it would have risen to 1,000 percent. 

00:28:55.600 --> 00:29:00.200
This is the so-called Argentine syndrome,
which others are more competent to discuss. 

00:29:00.200 --> 00:29:03.600
It was a dilemma:
we could have total anarchy or order.

00:29:03.600 --> 00:29:07.600
The first step was the elimination of inflation,
that most unjust of taxes.

00:29:07.600 --> 00:29:12.280
Secondly, restructuring.
We created a serious restructuring department. 

00:29:12.280 --> 00:29:16.920
Later on the rehabilitation
of the banks and measures

00:29:16.920 --> 00:29:18.880
which had been in the planning
stages for ten years.

00:29:18.880 --> 00:29:21.840
The first part of the programme was
implemented very efficiently. 

00:29:21.840 --> 00:29:25.840
The Croatian currency dinar was stabilised,
and finally the crowning moment

00:29:25.840 --> 00:29:29.999
of the introduction of the Croatian kuna.

00:29:30.200 --> 00:29:36.840
To be quite honest, it is one of the most
important days in my career at the time,

00:29:36.840 --> 00:29:38.840
perhaps even my entire career.

00:29:39.040 --> 00:29:44.360
Absolutely positive effects - everyone who
has participated in it can feel proud,

00:29:44.360 --> 00:29:46.840
especially the economic team
as the authors of the programme,

00:29:47.040 --> 00:29:52.360
led by Vice-President Škegro
and Governor Jurković.

00:29:56.080 --> 00:29:58.080
INTRODUCTION OF THE KUNA

00:30:13.600 --> 00:30:22.280
The introduction of the kuna in 1994
- and it happening on our Independence Day

00:30:22.280 --> 00:30:24.880
- was in some ways,

00:30:24.880 --> 00:30:31.920
Dr. sc. Hrvoje Klasić, historian
proof of the power held by
the Croatian authorities at that point,

00:30:31.920 --> 00:30:36.600
proof they were in control of
the situation to a much greater extent

00:30:36.600 --> 00:30:41.320
than it had in mid- and even late 1991.

00:30:43.000 --> 00:30:47.999
Dr. sc. Pero Jurković,
Governor of the NBC
from 1992 to 1996
That we have reached this great day
is due to the results of a diligent,

00:30:47.999 --> 00:30:51.840
Dr. sc. Pero Jurković,
Governor of the NBC
from 1992 to 1996
wise and principled overall and
economic policy in Croatia.

00:30:51.840 --> 00:30:55.480
This act is also evidence of
the solid and clear commitment

00:30:55.480 --> 00:30:59.400
of our country and its leadership to peaceful
politics and a policy of economic

00:30:59.400 --> 00:31:04.760
revival based on versatile Croatian
involvement in contemporary

00:31:04.760 --> 00:31:08.200
European and world economics.

00:31:08.200 --> 00:31:12.720
However, the greatest contribution to
this celebration has been by the ordinary

00:31:12.720 --> 00:31:16.880
people and citizens of Croatia,
who have patiently borne the brunt

00:31:16.880 --> 00:31:21.080
of the war and the stabilisation programme,
and who are still willing to give

00:31:21.080 --> 00:31:24.880
their all for the freedom, development
and prosperity of this country,

00:31:24.880 --> 00:31:27.520
our dear and only Croatia.

00:31:27.520 --> 00:31:31.000
Special thanks go to you, Mr. President,
who has been there every

00:31:31.000 --> 00:31:34.200
step of the way, to provide us
with the advice and support

00:31:34.200 --> 00:31:36.920
needed to persevere in this work.

00:31:36.920 --> 00:31:42.440
With God's help, may our kuna and lipa
have luck and sail calm waters

00:31:42.440 --> 00:31:46.200
on their way to joining a society of stable
and globally recognized currencies.

00:31:47.080 --> 00:31:51.520
The kuna was a very important element
in the defense of the country

00:31:51.520 --> 00:31:53.960
- moral, material and psychological.

00:31:55.120 --> 00:31:59.720
Dr. sc. Franjo Tuđman
first Croatian President
At all times and in all countries,
the introduction of a national currency

00:31:59.720 --> 00:32:05.400
Dr. sc. Franjo Tuđman
first Croatian President
has had great significance in a moral,
political and psychological sense

00:32:05.400 --> 00:32:07.640
and consequently, the economic.

00:32:07.640 --> 00:32:13.240
I am convinced that the same will hold
true for the introduction of our own currency,

00:32:13.240 --> 00:32:15.240
the kuna and lipa.

00:32:15.240 --> 00:32:21.080
The Croatian people deserve this - in fact,
the Croatian people have

00:32:21.080 --> 00:32:31.280
contributed both politically and economically,
and unfortunately in war,

00:32:31.280 --> 00:32:36.000
defending their homeland, defending
against aggression - because today,

00:32:36.000 --> 00:32:39.280
the Croatian people hold their own
currency in their hands as a

00:32:39.280 --> 00:32:41.680
means to further their development.

00:32:45.680 --> 00:32:48.440
BANKNOTE LIFECYCLE

00:32:50.000 --> 00:32:54.800
Boris Raguž
Currency Department director, HNB
The life span of banknotes
issued in smaller denominations

00:32:54.800 --> 00:32:57.120
is somewhere up to 24 months, two years.

00:32:57.120 --> 00:33:02.800
For larger denominations the lifespan is longer,
3, 5 to 4 years. 

00:33:02.800 --> 00:33:10.240
Otherwise, the most used denomination,
with the greatest number of banknotes

00:33:10.240 --> 00:33:12.840
in circulation in Croatia, is HRK 200.

00:33:12.840 --> 00:33:18.200
This is primarily because banks use it for
payouts and for ATM withdrawals.

00:33:18.200 --> 00:33:23.000
When talking about quantities,
the 200 and 100 kuna banknotes

00:33:23.000 --> 00:33:27.880
make up almost 50% of the current circulation.

00:33:27.880 --> 00:33:31.680
Prof. dr. Vilko Žiljak
co-author of the kuna banknotes
The crown banknotes,
which evolved into the kuna,

00:33:31.680 --> 00:33:37.400
Prof. dr. Vilko Žiljak
co-author of the kuna banknotes
were created using vector graphics,
which means their lines are very fine.

00:33:37.400 --> 00:33:42.200
At the time, these fine lines were effective
against the very strong threat of photocopying.

00:33:42.200 --> 00:33:46.560
They were difficult to photocopy, almost impossible,
at least at that time,

00:33:46.560 --> 00:33:52.160
and the tradition of fine, super-thin
lines was continued to the extent 

00:33:52.160 --> 00:33:58.000
of using them for the lettering
- we are talking about microtext here,

00:33:58.000 --> 00:34:01.999
which is a character less than
one millimetre in height.

00:34:12.680 --> 00:34:17.600
The design has remained the same,
but we have added some new protective elements.

00:34:17.600 --> 00:34:23.880
Prof. Miroslav Šutej
designer and co-author
of the kuna banknote
There were few interventions,
we added new elements for protection and they

00:34:23.880 --> 00:34:26.160
they have given a new image
to the banknote.

00:34:26.160 --> 00:34:31.040
The upgrade of the existing series
of banknotes has proved to be very

00:34:31.040 --> 00:34:35.440
successful because during
these twenty years of using,

00:34:35.440 --> 00:34:41.800
kuna banknotes have a practical average
of around 1,000 counterfeits detected annually.

00:34:41.800 --> 00:34:50.360
To illustrate, if we start with the current
circulation figure of 160 million banknotes, 

00:34:50.360 --> 00:34:57.520
that is two counterfeits to every
million registered banknotes,

00:34:57.520 --> 00:34:59.960
an almost negligible number.

00:35:04.400 --> 00:35:06.960
FUTURE

00:35:25.480 --> 00:35:29.240
The future of the Croatian kuna is to
remain a stable currency

00:35:29.240 --> 00:35:34.080
Dr. sc. Boris Vujčić, HNB Governor
that will serve the basic goal of the HNB,
which is price stability,

00:35:34.080 --> 00:35:38.520
Dr. sc. Boris Vujčić, HNB Governor
which means- we have stable prices and
a stable currency, although it is not fixed. 

00:35:38.520 --> 00:35:43.480
There is no fixed exchange rate,
we let it fluctuate against the euro,

00:35:43.480 --> 00:35:49.480
but we cannot allow excessive exchange rate oscillations,
a policy the HNB will maintain in the future. 

00:35:49.480 --> 00:35:54.880
One of the main goals of our monetary
policy is to maintain the kuna 

00:35:54.880 --> 00:36:01.280
at a stable exchange rate until
the introduction of the euro. 

00:36:01.280 --> 00:36:09.440
Why? Because Croatia is a very highly
euroised country, citizens' loans

00:36:09.440 --> 00:36:14.360
as well as those of businesses and even
the state are tied to the euro exchange rate; 

00:36:14.360 --> 00:36:20.200
any significant fluctuations, such as a falling
kuna exchange rate to the euro,

00:36:20.200 --> 00:36:26.080
would in fact lead to an increase in debt.

00:36:26.080 --> 00:36:31.720
Excessive strengthening of the euro would not
have a good effect on Croatia's competitiveness, 

00:36:31.920 --> 00:36:34.920
therefore the obvious choice
is to maintain a stable exchange rate

00:36:34.920 --> 00:36:37.040
until the introduction of the euro.

00:36:37.040 --> 00:36:43.960
Mr. sc. Borislav Škegro
NBC Council member from 1992 to 1997
And if you look at the twenty-year history
of the fluctuation of the free floating exchange rate,

00:36:43.960 --> 00:36:50.600
Mr. sc. Borislav Škegro
NBC Council member from 1992 to 1997
you will see that the kuna is one of the few currencies
that has maintained the highest degree of stability, 

00:36:50.600 --> 00:36:53.400
formerly in relation the German mark
and to the euro today.

00:36:53.400 --> 00:37:00.600
Prof. dr. Kuzma Kovačić
sculptor, author of the kuna and lipa coins
I am a little sad at the idea, if the Croatian
currency is someday replaced by the euro.

00:37:00.600 --> 00:37:07.520
If it proves necessary,
it would be nice for the Croatian

00:37:07.520 --> 00:37:17.800
euro to retain some part of this visual design
for the kuna and lipa.

00:37:18.520 --> 00:37:23.720
Well, for the euro to be introduced at the moment,
from the perspective of where we are today,

00:37:23.720 --> 00:37:29.440
the most important task will be to bring
public debt under control.

00:37:29.440 --> 00:37:34.360
We know that public debt has grown
rapidly since the beginning of the crisis,

00:37:34.360 --> 00:37:39.800
we know that in order to enter the eurozone
the state must meet the so-called Maastricht criteria

00:37:39.800 --> 00:37:46.600
relating to the budget deficit and public debt,
the inflation rate, the exchange rate,

00:37:46.600 --> 00:37:50.040
which must be stable, and interest rates.

00:37:50.040 --> 00:37:55.880
At the moment, our biggest problem is
the rapid growth of public debt.

00:37:55.880 --> 00:38:02.920
We can begin to talk about joining the eurozone
only when we push the growth trajectory

00:38:02.920 --> 00:38:06.800
of public debt in GDP downwards.

00:38:06.800 --> 00:38:10.960
Only then will we be ready to start a discussion
and meet the other Maastricht criteria.

